extends layout

block content
    .page-hero
        h2.page-title= title
        p.page-subtitle Last updated: #{effectiveDate}

    .content-panel.my-4
        .legal-body
            p Welcome to Katyusha ("the Bot"), a Discord bot that provides card search and utility features for the KARDS community. By adding, inviting, or using the Bot on a Discord server, or by interacting with the Bot in Direct Messages, you agree to these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree with these Terms, please do not use the Bot.

            h3.legal-heading 1. Description of the Service
            p Katyusha is a prefix-command Discord bot. Users invoke commands by sending messages that begin with the Bot's configured prefix (for example, #[code !search]). The Bot ignores messages that do not begin with the configured prefix. The primary functionality of the Bot is to perform searches against an external card database and return the corresponding card images and information to the user.

            h3.legal-heading 2. Acceptable Use
            p You agree to use the Bot only for its intended purpose and in compliance with Discord's #[a.data-link(href="https://discord.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer") Terms of Service] and #[a.data-link(href="https://discord.com/guidelines" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer") Community Guidelines]. You agree not to:
            ul.legal-list
                li Abuse, overload, or attempt to disrupt the Bot or the services it relies on.
                li Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Bot, its host systems, or its data.
                li Use the Bot for any unlawful, harmful, or abusive activity.
                li Circumvent any rate limits, access controls, or usage restrictions.

            h3.legal-heading 3. User Data and Permissions
            p By using the Bot, you acknowledge that your Discord username, avatar, and bot commands may be processed for the purpose of providing the Bot's functionality. This information is not publicly accessible and is visible only to Bot administrators.
            p The Bot processes only user messages that are valid bot commands. Messages that are not directed to the Bot are ignored and are not processed or stored.
            p Command data may be stored and analyzed to improve the Bot's search functionality, maintain service quality, and generate aggregated usage statistics. The Bot does not collect or archive general conversations.

            h3.legal-heading 4. Access Restrictions
            p We may restrict your usage of the Bot without your consent and without any explanation.

            h3.legal-heading 5. Availability
            p The Bot is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. We make no guarantee that the Bot will be available, uninterrupted, or error-free. We may modify, suspend, or discontinue the Bot, or any of its features, at any time and without prior notice.

            h3.legal-heading 6. Third-Party Services
            p The Bot operates on the Discord platform and relies on external services and data sources, including an external card database. Your use of Discord is governed by Discord's own terms and policies. We are not responsible for the content, availability, or practices of any third-party services.

            h3.legal-heading 7. Intellectual Property
            p Card names, images, and related content returned by the Bot are the property of their respective owners. The Bot merely retrieves and displays this content in response to user requests. All trademarks and copyrights belong to their respective holders.

            h3.legal-heading 8. Disclaimer of Warranties
            p To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Bot is provided without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.

            h3.legal-heading 9. Limitation of Liability
            p To the fullest extent permitted by law, in no event shall the operators of the Bot be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising out of or related to your use of, or inability to use, the Bot.

            h3.legal-heading 10. Changes to These Terms
            p We may update these Terms from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. Your continued use of the Bot after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the revised Terms.

            h3.legal-heading 11. Contact
            p If you have any questions about these Terms, please open an issue on the project's GitHub repository at #[a.data-link(href="https://github.com/alex-weber/katy-kards-bot/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer") github.com/alex-weber/katy-kards-bot].

    p &nbsp;
